= Creation Guide =

== Picking the Right Race ==

Magicians must take into account a number of things.  None of the pure caster class races have any experience penalties associated with them.  A lot of Magicians choose the [[Erudite]] race since it has the highest base intelligence.  [[Human]]s are popular for their rounded stats, and [[Dark Elf|Dark Elves]] for their high agility and racial ability to Hide, though they are often killed on sight in many places.  Conversely, [[Gnome]]s are generally well liked in most places.

== Starting Statistics ==

[[File:magician-stats.png]]

== Suggested Starting Statistics ==

It is very easy to assign yourself the wrong statistics and regret it for the rest of you characters career.  Magicians are primarily about mana, and our suggested allocation of bonus points reflects this:

* For Dark Elves add 25 Intelligence and 5 Stamina.
* For Erudites add 25 Intelligence and 5 Agility. This will keep you from taking the <75 AGI massive AC hit.
* For Gnomes add 25 Intelligence and 5 Stamina.
* For High Elves add 25 Intelligence and 5 Stamina.
* For Humans add 25 Intelligence and 5 Stamina.

''(This section needs a realistic/modern update for p1999.)''

== Experience Statistics ==

As of the January 2001 timeline patch, the class penalty was removed ([https://www.project1999.com/forums/showthread.php?t=211758 September 21, 2015]).

'''What does it mean?'''

Certain races and classes require differing amounts of experience points to attain the same level. For example, a Human Magician requires 110% of the experience that a Human Cleric would require to be the same level.


== Religion ==

Generally speaking being agnostic is a fairly safe bet in Everquest. Follower of [[Tunare]] can quest for [[Chord of Vines]].


